race.comment: TOURNELLE (3) got the blinkers on last start and it proved the difference, looming up strongly and racing away to win impressively at Sandown Hillside last time out to break a long run of placings. The time was good there and she'll get every chance from barrier three with D Lane booked to ride. KHADIME (10) was poor first up as a $2.60 chance at Sale, dropping right out there. Take on trust, but her form last time in reads very well for a race like this and she could bounce back quickly. HAPPY LINK (8) continues to race well, placing in her past three trying hard behind a smart type last start. She'll run another honest race and be in the finish. SIRENA (7) resumes. She's finished in the quinella at 4/8 starts and put up some decent performances in 3yo company. She draws well and can measure up.
